{
  "texts": [
    "The latter means that a transition may occur even if it is highly unlikely.An RL agent interacts with the environment in discrete time.",
    "At every time step t, the agent observes the state s t of the environment.",
    "It then chooses an action a t w.r.t a current policy π.",
    "The environment then moves to a state s t+1 with probability T (s t, a t, s t+1) and gets the reward r t = r(s t, a t, s t+1).",
    "Formally, a policy π is a mapping from states of the environment to actions the agent will perform."
  ]
}